## Dev Notes

### Architecture Context
- Project migrated from Tailwind CSS to Blueprint.js v6 (Session 015)
- Blueprint.js provides Intent system for semantic colors (SUCCESS, WARNING, DANGER)
- Current components use mix of:
  - Blueprint Intent colors (semantic)
  - MMS CSS custom properties (--mms-*)
  - Hardcoded hex values in inline styles (need fixing)

### Technical Approach
1. Preserve Blueprint's Intent system (it's semantic and accessible)
2. Add MMS-specific tokens for brand identity
3. Replace all inline hardcoded colors with CSS variable references
4. Use CSS custom properties for consistency across Blueprint and custom components

### Files to Modify
- apps/web/src/app/globals.css (tokens)
- apps/web/src/components/**/*.tsx (14 component files)
- docs/design/DESIGN_TOKENS.md (new documentation)

